                <h4>Classroom Observation Tool (COT)</h4>

            </span>
            <p>The Classroom Observation Tool captures snapshots of a  teacher&rsquo;s behavior and instruction during classroom observation visits that can  be used to develop improvement plans and track a teacher&rsquo;s progress over time.  The system is well aligned with the Texas Prekindergarten Guidelines and can be  used by teachers, school leaders, and intervention specialists to promote  effective teaching.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Item level indicators are highly targeted and  easy to establish as goals for improvement.</li>
                <li>The indicators focus on evidence-based teaching  behaviors that research has shown improve child outcomes.</li>
                <li>The design ensures age, linguistic, and cultural  appropriateness (e.g., for dual language learners).</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
