                <h4>Classroom Environment Checklist (CEC)</h4>

            </span>
            <p>Similar to the Classroom Observation Tool, the Classroom Environment Checklist (CEC) is a quality evaluation tool designed to track improvement over the time. The CEC’s focus is the presence and quality level of instructional planning tools (e.g. lesson plans, progress monitoring tools), meaningful literacy and print centers and materials (e.g. letter wall, availability of books), and the overall design and management of the classroom and individual centers (e.g. labeling centers, providing writing tools).</p>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <span>
                <h4>Collaboration Tools</h4>
            </span>
            <p>A key component of Texas School Ready! implementation is coaching, which offers an opportunity to provide one-on-one professional development support to teachers in the classroom.  Through CLI Engage, school and district specialists can interact with teachers and provide coaching support.  CLI Engage will include collaboration tools that will enable schools to create coaching plans for teachers, assign professional development to meet a teacher’s individual needs, upload classroom videos, and offer one-on-one feedback, all through one system to track teacher progress.</p>
        </li>
