<div class="left-container">
    <h4>Additional Support Services</h4>
    <p>
        In addition to all the open access components housed on CLI Engage, TSR continues to provide more customized technical assistance at no cost to districts through a competitive, needs-based application process.  More information on the application process will be released in Summer 2015.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Two-Day CIRCLE Training</strong></p>
    <p>The CIRCLE 2-Day Teacher Training is a face-to-face introduction to the foundational, research-based concepts underpinning Texas School Ready! and the CIRCLE line of professional development tools. The goal of the training is to provide a strong knowledge base of early childhood development and quality instructional strategies that support it, so that moving forward teachers feel comfortable exploring eCIRCLE online courses and the CIRCLE Activity Collection on their own.</p>
    <p><strong>Video-based Coaching</strong></p>
    <p>CLI’s approach recognizes that some high-need schools and districts can realize greater child outcomes with individualized, one-to-one teacher coaching. Communicating with teachers via Skype, web-postings, and by phone, trained coaches provide guidance on the teacher’s own recorded instruction. Teachers can review feedback through annotations made directly on their videos as well. Coaches also share other videos of effective teaching and set data-driven goals with the teacher for instructional improvement.</p>
    <p>Video-based coaching increases TSR’s capacity to serve classrooms in communities with limited access to quality improvement opportunities by eliminating the costs associated with travel to remote schools.  With funding from the Department of Education’s Institute of Education Sciences, TSR recently began a 4-year study to measure the effectiveness of video-based coaching as compared with a traditional face-to-face model.</p>
    <p><strong>Developing Talkers Training</strong></p>
    <p>
        TSR will provide advanced training to teachers in high-need  districts in the Pre-Kindergarten Response to Intervention (P-RTI)  instructional framework and supplemental curriculum, Developing Talkers/Hablemos Juntos. These parallel English and Spanish versions are designed to  meet the needs of many aspects of Tier 1 and Tier 2 pre-K oral language  instruction. Specifically, listening comprehension and vocabulary skills are  targeted in the book reading context by providing lessons, materials, and an  instructional template to develop and strengthen children&rsquo;s oral language  skills.<br />
        Each Developing Talkers Kit includes four units:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Introductory Unit</li>
        <li>Unit 1 Binder: All About Me or Todo sobre mí</li>
        <li>Unit 2 Binder: Nature Around Us or Mi mundo</li>
        <li>Unit 3 Binder: Let&rsquo;s Learn About Animals or  Animale</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Each Unit Binder includes: </p>
    <ul>
        <li>(80) Tier 1 lesson plans and (64) Tier 2 for 16  weeks of instruction</li>
        <li>12 Weeks of Curriculum-Based Measures: Knowledge  of Target Vocabulary Words</li>
        <li>A Monthly Curriculum-Based Checklist: Language  and Comprehension Skills</li>
        <li>Vocabulary and picture cards for each week of  instruction</li>
        <li>(2) books per week for a total of (32) books</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Each book has discussion points inserted within the pages,  including a &ldquo;before reading&rdquo; label on the inside cover of the book, several &ldquo;during  reading&rdquo; stickers as the story moves along, and an &ldquo;after reading&rdquo; sticker at  the end of the book.</p>
